==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

In the bronze script, it was attested as {{zh-l|*𬔧}}, an {{Han compound|章|丮|ls=ic|t1=jade ornament|t2=to hold|nocap=1}} – holding a jade ornament > “to bestow”. The {{zh-l|*丮}} component corrupts into {{zh-l|*欠}} or {{zh-l|*次}}, and later to {{zh-l|*夂}} or a variant with {{zh-l|*二}} under {{zh-l|*夂}}. An additional semantic component {{zh-l|*貝|cowrie; money}} was often added. The {{zh-l|*二}} and {{zh-l|*貝}} components combine to form an emergent phonetic component {{och-l|貢}}.

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' reinterprets it as a {{Han compound|竷|貝|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=shell; money|abb1=y|nocap=1}}, but this is not supported by earlier scripts.

